SIMPLE: moneyed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moneyed
<hw>Mon"eyed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Supplied with money; having money; wealthy; <as>as,
<ex>moneyed</ex> men</as>.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>monied</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Converted into money; coined.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If exportation will not balance importation, away must your silver
go again, whether <qex>moneyed</qex> or not <qex>moneyed</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Consisting in, or composed of, money.</def>
<rj><au>A. Hamilton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moneyer</ent>⟦br⟧
